President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate James C. Miller, III to a key Administration post as Governor of the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. Miller is currently a Senior Advisor at the law firm Husch Blackwell LLP and previously served on the Board of Governors from 2003 to 2011. He was Chairman of the Board from 2005 to 2008 and also held other leadership positions within the organization. Miller has had an extensive career in government, including serving as Director of the Office of Management and Budget from 1985 to 1988 and Chairman of the Federal Trade Commission from 1981 to 1985. He is a member of various boards and institutions and holds degrees from the University of Georgia and the University of Virginia.